content.description: Slammer is just to the right of the large madrone tree at the base of Jailhouse Rock. Follow the bolt line up the seam and face just left of the upper arete.
content.protection: Fixe SS 3/8 double expansion, no chains
content.location: Refer to Rock Climbing Western Oregon Vol. 2: Umpqua map page 66-65, map 6 page 123.

content.description: Begins a few feet to the right of Slammer and the large madrone at the base of Jailhouse Rock. Climbs into the chimney-like feature just left of the upper arete.
content.protection: Fixe SS 3/8 double expansion, no chains
content.location: Refer to Rock Climbing Western Oregon Vol. 2: Umpqua map page 66-65, map 6 page 123.

content.description: Jailhouse is a small sandstone outcrop north of Treasure Island pinnacle. There are two established routes to the right side of a large madrone tree at the base of the rock. The wall receives a lot of shadowing so requires annual maintenance.
